# Local dev (pick ONE):
#
# A) Call FastAPI directly (must match how you open the site: CORS allows :3000 and :3001).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8003
#
# B) Same-origin proxy (no CORS): Next rewrites /api-proxy/* → FastAPI. Restart `npm run dev` after changing.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_VIA_PROXY=1
# Optional if API is not on 127.0.0.1:8003: CHEER_API_DEV_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:8003
#
# Production (pick ONE):
#
# A) Browser calls API directly — Cloud Run API must allow your site origin (CORS):
#    NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://YOUR-CHEER-SCORES-API.run.app
#    On the API set CHEER_SCORES_CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-exact-frontend-origin (required for custom domains;
#    *.run.app and *.vercel.app are allowed by default regex).
#
# B) Same-origin proxy (no CORS from the browser): set at build/runtime on the web host:
#    NEXT_PUBLIC_API_VIA_PROXY=1
#    CHEER_SCORES_API_PROXY_TARGET=https://YOUR-CHEER-SCORES-API.run.app
#    (Do not rely on NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL when using proxy — mvpApi uses /api-proxy.)

# Optional: default MVP competition (must exist in cheer_mvp_meets with synced data). Default is CHEERSPORT Atlanta.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_MEET_KEY=VARSITY-14478875
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_MEET_LABEL=2026 CHEERSPORT National All Star Cheerleading Championship
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_MEET_STATE=GA

# Optional: default gym filter on the MVP dashboard (case-insensitive). Default is All.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEFAULT_MVP_GYM=JPAC

# Tally feedback popup: form id from URL path (https://tally.so/r/xxxx → xxxx). Default is Cheer Tracker form 44LGjr.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TALLY_FEEDBACK_FORM_ID=

# PWA: register service worker on localhost so Chrome can show the “Add app” install prompt. Restart dev server after changing.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PWA_IN_DEV=1
